<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 30 at 10:29PM CDT until April 30 at 11:00PM CDT by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1100 PM CDT
FOR WESTERN ASHLEY COUNTY...
At 1029 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Old Milo, or 7
miles northwest of North Crossett, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Crossett, Hamburg, North Crossett, West Crossett, Fountain Hill, Old
Milo and Blanchton.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
